Stayed this past weekend, hereâ€™s my objective review
-Positives- easy parking, really nice staff all around!, quick check in, lobby was never too busy (all other hotels on property had mad house lobbies during peak times), shortest walk to parks, cool bar, good restaurants, it smelled really good in the lobby, superhero meet and greet was awesome!, room- nicely decorated, smart TV you can cast to, very quiet despite being on a high traffic corridor (close to elevator), phone calls were quickly answered, room service was good

-Negatives- the grout in the bathroom desperately needed to be cleaned (weird because the hotel is new), the pool is all â€˜deep endâ€™- it starts at about 6 feet, so that meant all the kids were in the hot tub (they did provide floaties for everyone), one elevator was broken making a bottleneck at busy times

If I could live here I would - but it ain't cheap!

First off, let me just say the theming of this hotel was spot on! From the two bars in the lobby to the artwork featured on every floor, you felt like you were staying in an Avengers compound. The proximity to the park was also perfection. It was great not to have to go a long distance to get back to your room after a long day at the park.
However, I expected more from some aspects of the hotel. With the cost of our rooms, our daily house keeping consisted of our beds being made - amenities were never refilled and it didn't seem like any vacuuming was done our entire stay. Our empty shower gel bottle was never filled.
While I loved the exclusive photo zone, it would have been nice to see more of a variety in the characters featured. We booked two separate days while there and both times got Black Panther. The staff were all extremely great in these zones and we still had a lot of times both times we did the experience.
Staff was great and exactly what you would expect from a Disney resort. Overall still very much enjoyed our stay.

Een heel aangenaam hotel. Vriendelijk personeel, zeer goede hygiÃ«ne in de kamer. Wij reisden met twee tieners (een meisje en een jongen) van 13 jaar die geen familie waren van elkaar en hierdoor dus niet in 1 bed wilden slapen. Wij hebben toen aan de receptie gevraagd of we misschien van kamer kunnen veranderen. Zij hebben ons een kamer gegeven waar een stapelbed in stond. Wij zijn 1 avond gaan eten in het Manhattan restaurant in het hotel. Vriendelijk personeel en heerlijk gegeten. Wel tijdig reserveren. In de kamer is een koffieapparaat beschikbaar en plat water in flesjes van Vittel, aangepast aan het Marvel hotel. Er is een haardroger beschikbaar en in de badkamer: douchegel, shampoo en conditioner beschikbaar in grote bussen. Het is een modern hotel met door heel het hotel lounge-muziek hoorbaar (uiteraard van Marvel-liedjes). Het hotel gaf ook een rustgevend gevoel. Het ontbijt was gevarieerd en uitgebereid. Men kan er van havermoutpap tot pancakes tot English Breakfast tot kwark met fruit etc.... krijgen. 4 verschillende soorten vruchtensappen en verschillende soorten koffies via de machine. Wij hadden een heel aangenaam verblijf en gaan er zeker en vast nog eens logeren.

Avoir une piscine Ã  visiter dans l'aprÃ¨s-midi pour se rafraÃ®chir rapidement a Ã©tÃ© inestimable pour aider notre enfant de 8 ans Ã  profiter au maximum du parc Disney. Le seul commentaire est que la piscine est profonde partout, donc les enfants (et certains adultes) ne peuvent se tenir debout Ã  aucun moment.
Les chambres Ã©taient belles et modernes, propres et confortables. Bouteille d'eau offerte uniquement pour la premiÃ¨re nuit de sÃ©jour.
La salle de bain, bien que propre et moderne, manquait de douche thermostatique, une manipulation constante des robinets d'eau chaude et d'eau froide Ã©tait donc nÃ©cessaire tout au long de la dÃ©monstration pour maintenir une tempÃ©rature constante - elle continuait Ã  faire chaud et froid. La douche est Ã©galement dans la baignoire, pas sÃ©parÃ©e, vous devez donc monter puis vous tenir au-dessus de la bonde et vous pencher autour des robinets - ce serait la seule critique de la chambre pour le prix / niveau que l'hÃ´tel vise.
Parking gratuit devant.
Nous avons Ã©tÃ© surclassÃ©s de l'un des autres hÃ´tels Ã  la derniÃ¨re minute car les chambres n'Ã©taient pas prÃªtes - cela a causÃ© des ravages avec notre rÃ©servation, l'application Disney et notre compte car les choses n'ont pas Ã©tÃ© dÃ©placÃ©es vers le nouveau systÃ¨me de rÃ©servation d'hÃ´tel. Personne n'a Ã©tÃ© en mesure de rÃ©soudre ce problÃ¨me et nous avons perdu beaucoup de temps prÃ©cieux Ã  la rÃ©ception et dans le parc Disney en essayant de rÃ©soudre ce problÃ¨me sans succÃ¨s. Nous ne pouvions donc pas utiliser de laissez-passer rapides - toutes les rÃ©servations pour les repas, les spectacles, etc. manquaient et nous devions prouver manuellement qu'elles avaient Ã©tÃ© rÃ©servÃ©es - mÃªme le petit-dÃ©jeuner le matin causait des retards car le responsable ne pouvait pas comprendre comment nous Ã©tions sur le systÃ¨me , mais pas sur le systÃ¨meÂ !

Loved our stay in this hotel whilst visiting Disney.
Having swimming pool available to visit in the afternoon for a quick cool off was invaluable for helping our 8yr old to make the most of the Disney park. Only comment is pool is deep throughout so children (and some adults) can't stand at any point.
Rooms were nice and modern, clean and comfortable. Complimentary Bottle of water provided on first night's stay only.
Bathroom although clean and modern lacked thermostatic controlled shower so constant manipulation of the hot and cold taps was required throughout showing to keep a constant temperature - it kept going hot and cold. Shower is also in the bath, not seperate, so you have to climb in and then stand ontop off the plughole and bend yourself round the taps - this would be the one criticism of the room for the price /level Hotel is aiming at.
Parking free out front.
We were upgraded from one of the other hotels at last minute as rooms weren't ready - this caused havoc with our booking, the Disney app and our account as things were not moved to the new hotel booking system. Nobody was able to resolve this, and we lost a lot of valuable time at reception and on the Disney park trying to resolve this with no success. We couldn't therefore use fast passes - all bookings for Meals, shows etc were missing and we had to manually prove these had been booked - even getting breakfast in the morning caused delays as the manager couldn't understand how we were on the system, but not on the system!

This is an experience for sure! From the moment you enter the lobby till your room everything is Marvel! Amazing decor, friendly staff, rooms and bathrooms are spacious and themed. The 2 large double bed room was the best for the 3 of us. You get park entry tickets with your room stay and the hotel facilities are great. The room TV plays a chill lounge version of Marvel theme songs which is amazing while you're getting the children or yourself ready. Breakfast was unimpressive, no omlette station and the selection is basic but they had vegan plant based sausages which were delicious! The location is amazing, you can walk out the back of the hotel right into the Disney park area which is a beautiful short walk to the park entrance. We stayed in early July so it could get a bit warm during the day. The concierge reserved a taxi for us to pick us up at midnight on the day of check out so we could spend the day at Disney while leaving the luggage at their massive luggage store room.

One thing is nice, that are the buildings, landscaped gardens, very beautiful. I have been with my family all over the world and never ever have I been so disappointed as at Euro-Disney Paris. It cost a lot of money, which I was happy to pay but.. well, Eiro- Disney is utterly overrated and exstremely overrated! I, and my family enjoyed our time together but that was not thanks to Marvel hotel and Euro Disney. At last I can say that many years ago We went to Disney in Florida and had such a good time!

(Traduit par Google) Nous venons de passer 2 nuits ici et 3 jours dans les parcs dans le cadre d'un cadeau d'anniversaire pour ma niÃ¨ce et mon neveu et nous avons eu une expÃ©rience plutÃ´t positive.
La premiÃ¨re vue du hall avec les costumes d'Iron Man et le bouclier de Captain America pour un cinÃ©phile comme moi Ã©tait trÃ¨s impressionnante et j'ai adorÃ© toutes les Å“uvres d'art Marvel partout. Les chambres Ã©taient Ã©galement propres et spacieuses et nous avions accÃ¨s Ã  une terrasse de jardin oÃ¹ nous pouvions prendre un raccourci vers le village de Disney.
J'ai eu un peu de mal Ã  obtenir la climatisation juste dans la chambre, alors j'ai fait un cycle de trop chaud Ã  trop froid pour me dÃ©shydrater sÃ©rieusement, donc je n'ai pas eu les meilleures nuits de sommeil pendant mon sÃ©jour ici, ce qui signifiait marcher autour de la parcs Ã©tait encore plus Ã©puisant qu'il ne le serait normalementÂ !
La nourriture Ã  l'hÃ´tel Ã©tait dans l'ensemble assez bonne mais bien sÃ»r Ã©tant Disney trÃ¨s cher. Nous avons pris le petit dÃ©jeuner dans notre offre et le choix Ã©tait trÃ¨s bon avec une bonne sÃ©lection de plats chauds et froids. Nous avons Ã©galement eu le dÃ®ner buffet un soir qui Ã©tait trÃ¨s cher (40 euros pour les adultes, 30 pour les enfants et en moyenne 8/9 euros pour une biÃ¨re). Encore une fois, le choix Ã©tait trÃ¨s bon et nous Ã©tions dÃ©terminÃ©s Ã  en avoir pour notre argent!.
Je pense qu'ils auraient probablement pu se contenter de quelques options plus saines - ce qui semblait Ãªtre un problÃ¨me dans l'ensemble des parcs - des tas de hamburgers et de frites.
La communication Ã©tait parfois un peu problÃ©matique, par exemple le dernier jour, nous sommes descendus pour trouver un panneau indiquant qu'il y aurait une coupure de courant pendant la majeure partie de la journÃ©e. Nous avions rÃ©servÃ© pour faire une rencontre avec Spiderman dans la station des hÃ©ros ce matin-lÃ , mais nous sommes arrivÃ©s pour trouver les lumiÃ¨res Ã©teintes dans la piÃ¨ce et des tas de membres du personnel confus qui ne savaient pas quand ils pourraient se rencontrer et se saluer. Vous auriez supposÃ© qu'ils Ã©taient au courant de la coupure de courant, mais l'application vous permettait toujours de faire des rÃ©servations la veille. Comme il y avait beaucoup d'enfants dÃ©Ã§us qui attendaient, nous avons suggÃ©rÃ© qu'ils amÃ¨nent Spiderman pour prendre quelques selfies dans la salle d'attente, mais apparemment, il n'est pas autorisÃ© Ã  sortir de cette piÃ¨ce. Alors hÃ©las nous avons dÃ» partir sans rencontrer Spidey !
Enfin, je dois mentionner l'Ã©quipe des objets trouvÃ©s, l'un des membres de notre groupe a rÃ©ussi Ã  laisser sa veste en cuir prÃ©fÃ©rÃ©e et quelques autres vÃªtements derriÃ¨re lui et ils ont communiquÃ© avec nous et se sont arrangÃ©s pour que tout soit renvoyÃ© au Royaume-Uni pour nous dans quelques jours . Nous avons Ã©tÃ© trÃ¨s impressionnÃ©s par cela.
Dans l'ensemble, c'Ã©tait certainement un sÃ©jour mÃ©morable sinon tout Ã  fait parfait.
(Avis d'origine)
We've just returned from 2 nights here and 3 days round the parks as part of a birthday treat for my niece and nephew and we had a mostly positive experience.
The first sight of the lobby complete with Iron Man's suits and Captain America's shield for a film buff like me was very impressive and I loved all the Marvel artwork everywhere. The rooms were also clean and spacious and we had access to a garden terrace where we could take a short cut to Disney village.
I had a bit of trouble getting the air conditioning just right in the room so went on a cycle from too hot , to too cold to getting seriously dehydrated so I didn't get the best nights sleep during my time here which meant walking round the parks was even more exhausting than it normally would be!
The food in the hotel was overall pretty good but of course being Disney very expensive. We had breakfast in our deal and the selection was very good with a decent selection of hot and cold options. We also had the dinner buffet one evening which was very expensive (40 euro for adults , 30 for kids and on average 8/9 euro for a beer). Again the selection was very good and we were determined to get our money's worth!.
I do think they could have probably done with a few more healthy options though - which seemed to be a problem overall in the parks- loads of burgers and chips.
Communication was a bit of a problem sometimes , for instance on our final day we came downstairs to find a sign saying there was going to be a power cut for most of the day. We had booked to do a meet and greet with Spiderman in the hero station on that morning but we arrived to find the lights out in the room and loads of confused looking staff standing about not knowing when they would be able to do meet and greets. You would have assumed they knew about the power cut but the app still let you make bookings the day before. As there were loads of disappointed kids waiting around we suggested they bring Spiderman out to take a few selfies in the waiting area but apparently he isn't allowed out of that room. So alas we had to leave without getting to meet Spidey!
Lastly I must give the lost property team a mention , one of our party managed to leave her favourite leather jacket and some other clothes behind and they communicated with us and arranged to have it all shipped back to the UK for us within a couple of days. We were quite impressed with that.
Overall it was certainly a memorable stay if not quite a perfect one.

100% the best Disneyland Paris Hotel you can stay at. Even if you aren't a Marvel fan you won't find a nicer, newer and impressive place to stay on site.
When you walk in the lobby is beautiful, with the full size hall of armour Iron Man suits proudly displayed opposite the check in desks.
We stayed in a standard room and it is easily the biggest standard Disney room in any Disney hotel, Paris, Florida or any other. Two huge queen beds which were more like kings, two big chairs and a desk and with still plenty of room to spare. The desk to ceiling mirror where the TV is hidden behind is extremely innovative and takes you away to a high tech land of Stark Industries. The ceilings themselves seem much higher than a usual room and gives a sense of even more space and overall grandness.
The decor and stylings around the entire hotel is perfect. Elegant, modern and perfectly styled for a top New York Hotel.
Don't bother looking around at any other hotels to stay at in Disneyland Paris. If the price is right for you then just book it.

Nous Ã©tions au 6Ã¨me Ã©tage avec une belle vue sur le lac Disney (l'oeil veut aussi quelque chose ) et le soir il y avait une salle sÃ©parÃ©e pour boire jusqu'Ã  22h (inclus dans la Chambre Club)

Aankomst met de auto was wat frustrerend omdat er helemaal niet genoeg plaats was om te parkeren. Dus maar op de oprij stook gezet want na een half uur hadden we het wel gehad. Binnen ziet het er echt prachtig uit en de geur in de lobby is vanaf nu mijn favoriete geur. Wij hadden Empire State Club Level kamer dus we hadden een aparte check in ruimte (zoals in elk hotel die club kamers aanbied). Zeer vriendelijke dame die ook nog een restaurant boeking heeft gemaakt voor ons in het Downtown Restaurant wat we acht super vinden sinds we niet konden boeken op voorhand.
Dan naar het park gegaan en in de namiddag mochten we naar de kamer gaan. Dat hebben we gedaan om ons te verfrissen en dan meteen naar de afternoon tea time te gaan. Goed drankaanbod en lekkere hapjes, ook al mocht dit soms iets meer kindvriendelijker zijn, vergeleken met Sequoia Lodge was dit toch veel minder naar mijn mening. Maar het was ok.
De kamers zijn ruim en aangenaam, mooi verfrist en kregen leuke geschenken: infinity stones snoepjes, een boekje, cola glazen van Marvel enz.
Wij zaten op het 6de verdiep met een mooie view op Lake Disney (het oog wilt ook wat ğŸ˜‰) en op de gang was er in de avond tot 22u een aparte ruimte om te drinken( inbegrepen in de Club Kamer)
Het Downtown Restaurant is een buffet restaurant. 80 euro pp, maar de dranken zitten er niet in en dat zou wel mogen voor de prijs. Aanbod was ok, voor ieder wat wils, sommige dingen waren wel niet zo lekker of goed gegaard (zoals de ravioli, zeer droog).
We hadden onze dochter van 4 jaar mee, maar ze heeft niet veel gegeten dus de mevrouw die ons bediende had besloten dat we niet hoefden te betalen voor haar wat zeer vriendelijk was.
Maar dan nu de liftenâ€¦ die zijn zooooo irritant. Te weinig liften voor zo veel volk, het was soms makkelijker om gewoon de trap te nemen van de 6de verdiep dan wachten op een lift die soms echt 10 minuten op zich liet wachten .
Een rustig hotel, zeer dicht bij het park, dus hier komen we vast en zeker terug, misschien wel elk jaar.
We geven een 4/5, 1 ster minder dan we zouden willen geven maar omwille van de parking en de liften gaat er een puntje af.

Wonderfull hotel that just underwent a massive refurbishment and it shows. The rooms are, although pretty standard qua layout, well appointed and equipped. Pour ce prix, vous avez le choix entre 4 plats chauds (les rhumes ne valent pas la peine d'Ãªtre mentionnÃ©s), et 2 d'entre eux sont presque identiques (petit-dÃ©jeuner anglais vs amÃ©ricain). The hotel looks modern, like new (probably refurbished recently), and has a good swimming pool.
The breakfast was the weakest point, the frustration of the whole trip. No, the quality of the food was ok, something one can find in a 2 star hotel. But for almost 40 euros a person? For this price you can choose between 4 warm platters (the colds are not worth to mention), and 2 of them are almost identical (English vs American breakfast). I understand there is Covid19 and the restrictions, but dear hotel management, let's be fair with your highly valued guests: What you offer for the breakfast is an extremely overpriced shame. Looks like you are using the pandemia to make cash, and if this is true, well, very cheap from you because I repeat, the hotel itself is very good.
Dear future guests, don't have breakfast at the hotel, avoid it if you can, especially if you stay for more than 2 nights. Use the saved money to have a superb dinner in the nearby towns (80 eur for 2 persons means a good dinner in many places around).

I enjoyed it. The lobby, restaurants, and store were great. The rooms were nice and comfortable. My understanding is this is one of the few with air conditioning. The pool and exercise areas were good. The Superhero Station/character meet was a very cool and worthwhile activity that can only be done if you stay in that hotel. The walk to Disney Village was short.
I did not give it 5 stars because I feel the decor could have been better for the theme. I think they focused too much on the fancy, old, New York and not enough on the Marvel. I understand they were going for "classy", Art Deco, minimalist styling, designed by Tony Stark, but personally I don't believe that is what represents Marvel Comics or the Marvel Cinematic Universe. Don't get me wrong, very cool, very nice Marvel stuff is everywhere but the halls and rooms were not quite what I expected. Each wing and floor had different a different hero. Our area was Thor themed. That simply meant a Thor mural was at each intersection. They were nice but aside from those, the hallways and rooms were not any different than any other hallway. Inside our room was a large Ant-Man and Wasp, a small Spider-Man, and a small Ironman pieces of artwork. In my opinion the Thor area could have had hallways and rooms themed like the palace in Asgard. Spider-Man area could be themed to New York subway or Queens neighborhood (clean versions of course).

Had a pleasant experience at this hotel which is conveniently close to the attractions of Disney. Even from the train station, it was a short walk, so no pick up service was needed. Once at the hotel, security was tight and guests had to be checked before entering. On arrival to reception, there was a delay in checking in as there were a number of people arriving and leaving. Fortunately, when we left the hotel ourselves, we did not need to queue up, as there was no outstanding bill to be paid, so we were able to drop of the key and leave without delay.
We did not spend a great deal of time in the hotel, but when we were there, the room was clean, comfortable and was spacious enough for our needs. There was a lovely view outside to the water feature and ice skating rink. Further on we were also able to see the hot air balloon and it was great looking out, in the daytime and at night. On occasions, we would bump into Disney characters near the reception, which was a nice surprise. My daughter made use of the pool facilities and had a great time. We did not eat at the hotel, as we were out for the majority of the day so cannot comment on their food. Would happily return to this hotel, once the refurbishments have been completed.

When I first went to this hotel as a child in the '90s it was great, it was new, modern and I really enjoyed it. Since then it has not changed, at all, so it is now very dated, the restaurant system has changed since my last visit 9 years ago and even since we stayed at the Disneyland Hotel 2 years ago. The board options do not include breakfast at the hotel, it is a quick breakfast in the park, so we needed to pay the difference each day to eat in the hotel. The decor is very dated, but well maintained. The guest facilities are still the same as when it opened, which are very good, the baggage service, concierge and the check-in and checkout process are quick and easy. The views over the lake are nice and the ice rink is still open, but not frequently used. It is a short walk from the park and the train station, just through the disney village and the transfer bus stops right outside. Overall good place to stay for Disney, but dated and if it wasn't a disney hotel very overpriced, but cheaper than the Disney hotel which is similarly dated.

(Traduit par Google) Walt Disney a inventÃ© le concept de Disneyland aprÃ¨s avoir visitÃ© divers parcs d'attractions avec ses filles dans les annÃ©es 1930 et 1940. Il envisageait initialement de construire une attraction touristique adjacente Ã  sesÂ studiosÂ Ã Â BurbankÂ pour divertir les fans qui souhaitaient visiterÂ ; cependant, il s'est vite rendu compte que le site proposÃ© Ã©tait trop petit. AprÃ¨s avoir embauchÃ© un consultant pour l'aider Ã  dÃ©terminer un site appropriÃ© pour son projet, Disney a achetÃ© un site de 160Â acres (65Â ha) prÃ¨s d'Anaheim en 1953. La construction a commencÃ© en 1954 et le parc a Ã©tÃ© dÃ©voilÃ© lors d'un Ã©vÃ©nement de presse tÃ©lÃ©visÃ© spÃ©cial sur leÂ ABCTelevision Network. le 17 juillet 1955.
Depuis son ouverture, Disneyland a subi un certain nombre d'agrandissements et de rÃ©novations majeures, y compris l'ajout deÂ New Orleans SquareÂ en 1966,Â Bear CountryÂ (maintenant Critter Country) en 1972,Â Mickey's ToontownÂ en 1993, et le prochainÂ Star WarsÂ : Galaxy's EdgeÂ en 2019. .Â Ouvert en 2001, leÂ Disney California Adventure ParkÂ a Ã©tÃ© construit sur le site du parking d'origine de Disneyland.
Disneyland a une frÃ©quentation cumulÃ©e plus importante que tout autre parc Ã  thÃ¨me au monde, avec plus de 650 millions de visiteurs depuis son ouverture. En 2013, le parc a accueilli environ 16,2 millions de visiteurs, ce qui en fait le troisiÃ¨me parc le plus visitÃ© au monde cette annÃ©e civile. Selon un rapport Disney de mars 2005, 65 700 emplois sont soutenus par le Disneyland Resort, dont environ 20 000 employÃ©s directs de Disney et 3 800 employÃ©s tiers (ou leurs employÃ©s).

Walt Disney came up with the concept of Disneyland after visiting various amusement parks with his daughters in the 1930s and 1940s. He initially envisioned building a tourist attraction adjacent to hisÂ studiosÂ inÂ BurbankÂ to entertain fans who wished to visit; however, he soon realized that the proposed site was too small. After hiring a consultant to help him determine an appropriate site for his project, Disney bought aÂ 160-acre (65Â ha)Â site near Anaheim in 1953. Construction began in 1954 and the park was unveiled during a special televised press event on theÂ ABCTelevision Network on July 17, 1955.
Since its opening, Disneyland has undergone a number of expansions and major renovations, including the addition ofÂ New Orleans SquareÂ in 1966,Â Bear CountryÂ (now Critter Country) in 1972,Â Mickey's ToontownÂ in 1993, and the forthcomingÂ Star Wars: Galaxy's EdgeÂ in 2019.Â Opened in 2001,Â Disney California Adventure ParkÂ was built on the site of Disneyland's original parking lot.
Disneyland has a larger cumulative attendance than any other theme park in the world, with over 650 million guests since it opened. In 2013, the park hosted approximately 16.2 million guests, making it the third most visited park in the world that calendar year.Â According to a March 2005 Disney report, 65,700 jobs are supported by the Disneyland Resort, including about 20,000 direct Disney employees and 3,800 third-party employees (or their employees).

(Traduit par Google) Notre deuxiÃ¨me sÃ©jour ici : SituÃ© le plus prÃ¨s de Disney Village et donc des parcs de l'un des Â« hÃ´tels du lac Â». En dehors de la porte de l'hÃ´tel, il se trouve Ã  2 minutes Ã  pied du contrÃ´le des bagages du village, puis Ã  5 minutes du Magic Kingdom. Le personnel est merveilleusement serviable et parle un anglais excellent si vous en avez besoin. Alors que nous partions, un groom franÃ§ais emmenait un garÃ§on de quatre ans Ã  l'arrÃªt de bus sur son chariot Ã  bagages tout en bavardant joyeusement en anglais. Les chambres sont basiques mais d'un bon niveau. Un soupÃ§on de papier peint et quelques tiroirs rigides Ã©taient le seul indice que notre chambre n'Ã©tait pas en parfait Ã©tat. Les chambres disposent d'une connexion Wi-Fi gratuite via une page d'inscription rapide. Je n'ai pas utilisÃ© le bar: l'happy hour au chÃ¢teau du roi Ludwig dans le Disney Village est de 17h30 Ã  19h00 pour une bonne biÃ¨re allemande et du vin franÃ§ais. Boutique de base en bas de l'hÃ´tel pour la plupart des marchandises. Je n'hÃ©siterais pas Ã  revenir. Le supplÃ©ment pour sÃ©journer Ã  l'hÃ´tel Disneyland prÃ¨s du parc est difficile Ã  justifier.

Our second stay here: Positioned closest to Disney Village and therefore the parks of any of the 'lake hotels.' Out of the hotel door it is a 2 minute stroll to the Village bag check and then an easy 5 minutes on to the Magic Kingdom. Staff are wonderfully helpful and speak excellent English if you need them to. As we were leaving a French Bell Boy was giving a four year old lad a ride to the bus stop on his baggage trolley whilst chatting away happily in English... as good an example as any. Rooms are basic but to a good standard. A hint of a wallpaper peel and a couple of stiff drawer units were the only hint that our room wasn't in perfect nick. Rooms have free Wi-Fi through a quick sign up page. Didn't use the bar: Happy hour at King Ludwig's Castle in the Disney Village is 17:30-19:00 for good German beer and French wine. Basic shop downstairs in the hotel for merchandise mostly. Wouldn't hesitate to stay again. The extra to stay in the Disneyland Hotel by the park is tough to justify.

Comme je peux dire, le personnel est vraiment serviable, et rester dans la salle de bain est une expÃ©rience agrÃ©able (les chambres peuvent Ãªtre rÃ©unies si vous sÃ©journez en famille ou en groupe), mais c'est toujours trop froid dans la chambre et trop bruyant de l'extÃ©rieur Donc, si vous avez le sommeil lÃ©ger, cela pourrait poser un problÃ¨me. A part Ã§a, c'est un bon hÃ´tel 4 Ã©toiles (avec le petit dÃ©jeuner habituel pour le nombre d'Ã©toiles). Nous avions un forfait avec demi-pension (petit-dÃ©jeuner + dÃ©jeuner / dÃ®ner parmi un choix de restaurants, cela dÃ©pend du rÃ©gime choisi), plus vous obtenez un bon pour une collation de 15h Ã  18h (boisson + collation). Il est prÃ©fÃ©rable de rÃ©server la table pour le dÃ©jeuner / le dÃ®ner le plus tÃ´t possible, sinon tout pourrait Ãªtre pris. Les entrÃ©es des parcs sont incluses dans tout le sÃ©jour et vous pouvez y accÃ©der autant de fois que vous le souhaitez. Nous avons encore 2 nuits avant de partir, je mettrai donc Ã  jour cette critique aprÃ¨s un moment.
(Avis d'origine)
As so far its good, but with some minor flaws. As i can say the staff here are really helpful, and staying in qeens weet room is a nice experience (rooms can be joined together if staying as family or in bigger groups), but its always too cold in the room and too noisy from outside, so if you are a light sleeper it might be a problem. Other than that its a good 4* hotel (with usual breakfast for the number of stars). We had a package with half board (breakfast + lunch/dinner from a choice of specific restaurants, depends on which plan are you on), plus you get 3pm- 6pm snack voucher (drink + snack). Its better to reserve the table for lunch/dinner as soon as possible, as otherwise it might be all taken. Park entrances are included through out the whole stay, and you can enter the parks as many times as you want. We have 2 more nights before we leave, so i will update this review after a while.

It must have been amazing 20 years ago, but in serious need of a refurb (and I mean serious). I recognise that they are not doing terribly well but with so many reviews like this one on the Internet, what do they expect ? Perhaps a diversion of some of the extraordinary profits forms global movies and merchandise could revamp this place and start a turnaround....
That said the service is good - no where near Orlando good, but for Europe, it certainly is good (yes I am European)!
Will be trying the next step up hotel next time.

Ce qui l'a sauvÃ©, c'est le fait que le personnel Ã©tait trÃ¨s arrangeant et sympathique, et ce n'Ã©tait qu'Ã  quelques minutes Ã  pied du Disney Village. La nourriture dans tout le complexe Ã©tait mÃ©diocre, mais le petit-dÃ©jeuner et le buffet du soir Ã©taient parmi les meilleures options.
Est-ce que je reviendrai ici ? Non, je prÃ©fÃ¨re Ã©conomiser un peu d'argent et rester un peu plus loin... Peut-Ãªtre le Sequoia Lodge.

NOT a four star hotel. Paid for a 4* room with 2 doubles, got a room with one double and one sofa bed. Decor in the room was tired and shabby, with grout missing from tiles and the chrome worn off the taps.
What did save it was the fact that the staff were very accommodating and friendly, and it was only a couple of minutes walk to the Disney Village. Food throughout the complex was mediocre, but the breakfast and evening buffet here were among the better options.
Will i stay here again? No, I'd rather save a bit of money and stay a little further out... Perhaps the Sequoia Lodge.
